from the third story and was picked up dead.
	--Acts 20:9
%
Paul went down, threw himself on the young man and put his arms around him. 
“Don’t be alarmed,” he said. “He’s alive!”
	--Acts 20:10
%
Then he went upstairs again and broke bread and ate. After talking until 
daylight, he left.
	--Acts 20:11
%
The people took the young man home alive and were greatly comforted.
	--Acts 20:12
%
We went on ahead to the ship and sailed for Assos, where we were going to take 
