	--Acts 24:9
%
When the governor motioned for him to speak, Paul replied: “I know that for a 
number of years you have been a judge over this nation; so I gladly make my 
defense.
	--Acts 24:10
%
You can easily verify that no more than twelve days ago I went up to Jerusalem 
to worship.
	--Acts 24:11
%
My accusers did not find me arguing with anyone at the temple, or stirring up a 
crowd in the synagogues or anywhere else in the city.
	--Acts 24:12
%
And they cannot prove to you the charges they are now making against me.
	--Acts 24:13
%
However, I admit that I worship the God of our ancestors as a follower of the 
Way, which they call a sect. I believe everything that is in accordance with 
the Law and that is written in the Prophets,
	--Acts 24:14
%
and I have the same hope in God as these men themselves have, that there will 
be a resurrection of both the righteous and the wicked.
	--Acts 24:15
%
So I strive always to keep my conscience clear before God and man.
	--Acts 24:16
%
